knowledge_graph.title: Plum
knowledge_graph.description: A plum is a fruit of some species in Prunus subg. Prunus. Dried plums are often called prunes, though in the United States they may be labeled as 'dried plums', especially during the 21st century.

related_questions.question: What is plum slang for?
related_questions.snippet: (vulgar, slang, usually in the plural) A testicle. [from 20th c.] (derogatory, chiefly UK) A fool, an idiot.

related_questions.question: What is the literal meaning of plum?
related_questions.snippet: 1. : any of various trees and shrubs (genus Prunus) of the rose family with globular to oval smooth-skinned edible fruits that are drupes with oblong seeds. also : the fruit. 2. : any of various trees with edible fruits resembling plums.

related_questions.question: Do you eat plum skin?
related_questions.snippet: The skin is edible, but if you want raw plums without the skin, drop into into boiling water for around 15 seconds, then plunge immediately into cold water and it should come away easily. If you're cooking plums, they're easier to skin afterwards.

buttons.subtitle: What Do Plums Taste Like?
buttons.title: Plum - Wikipedia
buttons.snippet: The taste of the plum fruit ranges from sweet to tart; the skin itself may be particularly tart. It is juicy and can be eaten fresh or used in jam-making or other recipes. Plum juice can be fermented into plum wine. In central England, a cider-like alcoholic beverage known as plum jerkum is made from plums.

buttons.snippet: A ripe plum is rich and seductive, but also ornery. Sweet, to be sure, but with an acidic spark and an astringent bite. Peaches are puppy dogs—sugary and desperate for your love. By contrast, plums are goats that won't stop chewing on your clothes.

buttons.title: Plums - Foodwise
buttons.snippet: The plum tree is a member of the genus Prunus, which also includes peaches, apricots, and nectarines. This grouping of fruit is more commonly referred to as stone fruit, a name that is derived from the hard pits that cover their seeds.
